Arrays In Java:
===============
Arrays are index based. They are used to store collection of data that is of the same data type.
Arrays are of fixed size, that means, once declread you cannt modify its size. They hold fixed data.
Array is the building Block of many data structures like List.

Arrays class:
============= 
In Java, there is a very important utility class called Arrays.
It is part of the java.util.Arrays package and it provides very helpful utility methods like:
    - Perfom binary search:
    - loop throught an array using stream and for each.
    - convert array to String
    - sort an array
    - split and array
    - compare two arrays

Two Dimension Array:
====================
- Used to implement grid applications
- Example --- TIC TAC TOE game
- has X and Y axis
